From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] wifi: mt76: mt7921: fix SDIO early return in
 mac_reset_work

In mt7921_mac_reset_work(), the SDIO early return path at line 678
returns without clearing hw_full_reset, clearing MT76_RESET, or
waking TX queues. This leaves the device in a permanently stalled
state:

- hw_full_reset remains true, blocking future operations
- MT76_RESET remains set, preventing TX scheduling
- TX queues remain stopped (ieee80211_stop_queues was called at
  the beginning of the function), causing a permanent TX stall

Add proper cleanup before the SDIO early return: clear hw_full_reset,
clear MT76_RESET, and wake TX queues.

Fixes: 9d25e573a37f ("mt76: mt7921: fix possible SDIO hang")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
index 1234567..abcdef5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt7921/mac.c
@@ -683,7 +683,9 @@ void mt7921_mac_reset_work(struct work_struct *work)
 		if (!ret)
 			break;
 	}
-	if (mt76_is_sdio(&dev->mt76) && atomic_read(&dev->mt76.bus_hung))
+	if (mt76_is_sdio(&dev->mt76) && atomic_read(&dev->mt76.bus_hung)) {
+		dev->hw_full_reset = false;
+		clear_bit(MT76_RESET, &dev->mphy.state);
+		ieee80211_wake_queues(hw);
 		return;
+	}

